Rating: 3
I thought these potatoes were great, but I have a couple of suggestions. I doubled the recipe and ended up putting way too many potatoes on the first pan that I used. The potatoes STEAMED instead of roasting. On the second & third pan, I spread them out, making sure that they weren't touching & that each potato (flesh side down) touched the pan. Those batches were so much more crispy! Also, I doubled the amount of oil since I was doubling the recipe, & I realized later that there seemed to be way too much oil. I'm not sure if you need to cut the oil for one recipe, but I would definitely reduce it if you're doubling the recipe. Over all, these potatoes got rave reviews.

Rating: 4
My family loved these potatoes. I reduced the cayenne by half and that was spicy enough for some the tender palates. They were tasty, moist on the inside, easy, and can be prepared ahead of time. I don't have garlic salt, so used garlic powder- a little less than 2 teasp. - we do like garlic. The first time I made these really stuck to the pan so Thank-you to Bethesda's suggestion to heat the pan and keep the flesh side down. The potatoes did not stick and were even better the second time.

