Rating: 4
This is a great recipe because you can be versatile with the ingredients and the timing. For example, I used hot pepper flakes instead of cayenne and chili and let the spuds roast for an extra 20 minutes while I was finishing up everything else. They were delicious and crispy--thank you to everyone who reinforced the idea of heating up the oil before tossing. I served them with a marinated grilled London broil and crisp-tender baby carrots and zucchini chunks.

