Rating: 3
These were good, but a little overwhelmingly flavored. I prefer using just a minced clove of fresh garlic and some herbs (esp. sage and rosemary.) The previous reviewer is right regarding sticking...Put your baking sheet in the oven, on a low rack position, and warm it up first. When at temperature, pour your potatoes out onto the hot sheet, and be sure that a large "flesh-side" of each potato piece is down against the pan. It is the contact with the hot pan in the hot oven that browns the pieces. Half way thru, remove the pan, and you should be able to flip each potato piece onto a new flesh-side with a pair of tongs.

Rating: 3
